YOWZER!!

That hurts.  You pull your hand back and notice that your fingers are covered in blood.
> smell blood

> smell blood
You raise your hand to your nose and take a sniff of the drying blood on your hand.  It smells a bit like the bag of lucky pennies you have at home.

Home... it seems so far away, yet so close.  You have a keen longing for it.

Somewhere deep in your mind, a fleeting image of your lucky bag of pennies dances just outside of your consciousness.  If only you could focus on that bag of pennies you might remember happier times.
> focus on pennies

> focus on pennies
You focus, I mean really focus, your thoughts on that lucky bag of pennies.  You remember...

You always kept the lucky bag of pennies on the nightstand next to your bed.  Your mom always told you that it could never hurt to have good luck with you even when you slept.  Ah... sleep.   You remember the smell of copper as you would fall asleep and the sweet light that would wake you up in the morning.

Dear mom opens your door, turns the light on, and leaves without closing the door.  She always used to try and wake you up that way.  The gentle bask of the light interrupts your REM sleep.

As your eyelids part, you notice a bar of light entering from the jamb of your now open bedroom door.

You're now aware of a shaft of light.
> focus on bar of light

> focus on bar of light
You focus, I mean really focus on your masculine sha... Oh.  That's embarassing.  You meant... ...Nevermind.  You focus your thoughts on the morning light.  You remember...

The sweet, soft light gently warms your eyes to the breaking morning sunshine.  You open your eyes slowly and you can see your room.  You sit up and hear the sounds of the radio on downstairs.  Your mom always loved listening to music in the mornings as she prepared your breakfast.

You hear a pitter-patter somewhere in the distance.
> focus on sound

> focus on sound
You focus, I mean really focus, your thoughts on that quiet tap-tap-tap.  You remember...

Christmas morning!  Your entire family spent the night at your house last night on Christmas Eve.  You sit up in bed and hear the pitter patter of excited little feet running through the hallways.  Even as a 29 year old, you leap out of bed and rush downstairs.  First on the agenda, mom's delicious Christmas morning breakfast!  You scarf down the food and rush to the tree.

Your family files in.  Now, however, they lack any excitement whatsoever.  In fact, some look sad and some look angered.  Silence...

Your mom is the first to speak.  "Son, Xanadu... We have come to a difficult conclusion."

She looks around at the other family members.  Aunt Betty... Uncle Harold... Twin cousins Lou and Schul... Nine month old baby niece, Jules... They all nod their heads yes, urging mother to continue.

"Xan, we have agreed that it is time for you to leave.  We do not want you here anymore.  You have worn out your welcome."  All of your family members point, in unison, toward the front door.  Speechless, shocked, and saddened, you shuffle toward the door in your Spider Man pajamas.  Your sweet grandmother opens the door and you walk outside.  As the door slams shut, you hear a cacophony of the hoots and hollers as a celebration ensues from the other side of the door.

Wait! You stand there, alone, in the bitter cold.  This isn't how it happened...

You now sense a feeling of bitter cold.
> focus on feeling of bitter cold

> focus on feeling of bitter cold
You focus, I mean really focus, your thoughts on that uncomfortable, bitter cold feeling pressing in all around you.

Your senses have reawakened... some what.  You see a bar of light creeping in under a door out in front of you.  You can hear what sounds like little feet tapping from somewhere high above you.  You notice a musty, moldy, metallic smell all around you.  There is a piercing cold that is creeping into your bones.
