It's dark.  It's cold.
> listen

> listen
With nothing better to do than drive yourself crazy, you listen intently to the noise.

It seems like... It seems like...

It seems like it is coming from over there.

And even though you cannot see anything, you turn your head toward the northern wall of this small room.  You walk slowly toward the noise and...

THUMP!

You walk face first into a very hard wall.  You sniffle and some liquid, blood or snot, you're unsure, defies gravity and shoots back up your nose... and with it... a faint, odd smell of something you can't quite identify.
> smell

> smell
You take a big whiff thinking that whatever is making that noise might also have a certain smell.  That odor.  What is that?  It smells like...

Just as you are about to identify the smell, you realize you were holding your breath and you forcibly let it out.  You feel your warm breath travel over your cold hands and downward toward the floor.

Your attention is drawn toward a very thin sliver of light at the base of the wall.
You are not sure how to get out of this room.  You can't even see.  All you can do is first listen to the noise of whatever is making that sound, second smell the odor, and finally, feel the coldness in the room.
> feel

> feel
You press your hands down to the cold floor near the sliver of light and it is no warmer there.  It is just as cold as every other part of the room.  You leave your hands on the icy, cold ground long enough to know that this isn't leading you anywhere other than to a daydream wishing you were back home next to your fireplace.

You remove your hands from the ground and place them into the pockets of your pants to warm them up.

What's this?  There is something hard in your pocket.  No, you creep, this cold dark room doesn't in the least turn you on in THAT way.  You take your hands out of your pocket and realize that you still have your Man Card.

A Man Card has been added to your inventory.
> reflect light with card

> reflect light with card
You slide your one possession into the very thin sliver of light.  The light reflects ever so slighty off the card and up into the dark room.  After a few minutes of tilting the card this way and that, you can just barely make out where the reflected light is falling on the walls.

With some more work, you use the card to scan every square inch of the room.  After about thirty minutes something finally catches your eye.  You notice a very tiny gleam of metal on the west wall.
> pull tiny bit of metal

> pull tiny bit of metal
