You hear the fall of heavy footsteps approaching behind the thick stone wall followed by what sounded like the popping up of a jam jar when first opened.  The center of the north wall begins to move.  You realize it is a door that blended so perfectly with the stone walls.  It opens and a very large man carrying a tool box appears in the doorway.

You scream, "Let me out now!" in as much of a demanding voice that you can muster.  The man dismisses you with a wave of the hand.

"The only way you are getting out of here is if you are dead.  Are you dead?" he asks in a thick accent.

Dejected, you shake your head no, for once wishing that you were actually dead so you could get out of this hole.

Before you can plead your case for release, the large handyman cracks you in the head with his metal tool box.  Everything goes black.

You bat your eyes and you squint at the incoming light.  You scrape yourself off the floor, rubbing your forehead with one hand and pressing the other against the wall to help keep you upright.
