You harken back to your thespian days...

You put your hand to your mouth and cough a little.  You pace the corners of the room thinking of the best way to feign your death.  "Arrrrrgghhhh."  You squat down into a standing fetal position and clutch your stomach with both hands.  In a final pirouette with death you spin to the ground and topple over face down into the cold hard ground.

You wait...

and wait...

and wait...
Just as you are about to accept that your acting career and your life is a dead end, you hear some faint footsteps from outside of the door and decide to wait a little longer.  The door opens and you hold your breath.

"Aww hell," you hear a voice grumble from behind you.  "We have another one."  The man's voice is interrupted by heavy breathing.  He grabs your ankles and begins to pull you from the room.  *HEAVE*, *HEAVE*... *HEAVE*.  Your body is being dragged across the rough stone floor one foot at a time.  His 'heaves' are punctuated a little longer each time.  With a final heave, your face, thankfully, transitions from a rough cold floor to a slightly smoother, less cold one.

*HEEEAAAAVVVVVEEEE* "Ugghhh."  The man lets go of your feet and they flop to the floor.  You hear some irregular and heavy footsteps around you...

"Ouch," you utter as one of those steps comes down on your ankle, another on your groin, and another on your face.  You open your eyes, preparing to make a run for it, but you see a man clumsily staggering around, clutching his chest.  He teeters in a narrow hallway, careening from one wall to another.  He looks down in your direction and locks eyes with you.  You see a confused expression cross his face before he lets out a final groan.  His eyes roll up in his head and he falls over directly on top of you.
