"...area, over by the weights.  I overheard a group of seven or eight whispering.  They hushed up when they noticed me coming."

The second man responds.  "But what did you hear?  You get any thing?  Dingo is expecting us to report soon."

"Well," the voice trails to a whisper again, "I'm pretty sure... this whole Long John Silver thing going on..."  The voice fades out.

The second voice is still mostly a hush, "...probably... coup on his... Dingo will NOT like... guess, the ringleader... you know..."

"Uh-huh... Mongo... influential for sure... like that?"

The response is louder and clearer this time, "I'm okay with blowing the whistle on that guy.  Never liked him anyway."

