If you remember correctly, the panel in the garage required a fifteen character input for the password.  After reading this post-it note, you should now have made note of fifteen characters.  Perhaps it's a coincidence, but you might now have the correct code to the garage door!  You quickly scan your memory and jot down the fifteen digits you remember from the post-it notes.

