A voice booms over the loud speakers, "If you know the enemy and know yourself, your victory will not stand in doubt; if you know Heaven and know Earth, you may make your victory complete."  You recognize that quote as a Sun Tzu quote from the famous book 'Art of War'.
> wait

> wait
Time passes.

Hidden in your little hidey-hole, you hear the elevator doors open.  Based on the footsteps that you can hear, it appears that two people have exited the elevator and are now in the room with you.

There is a brief silence before a voice says, "Speak freely."  You are surprised to hear a female voice with an American accent.  Who? you think to yourself...

The Sarlashkar responds, "Miss," the Sarlashkar begins, "As you know, about dozens of scientists were found dead in the laboratory just moments ago.  We think the escaped prisoner, Xanadu Magoo, is responsible."

There is a pause followed by some light footsteps.  *SMACK*  The sound is unmistakable.  You've been on the receiving end of a woman's hateful slap several times.

"This is YOUR fault, Benny," the woman yells loudly.  "I told you to keep an eye on him.  He is our only hope in getting that code.  And, now, our scientists are dead and Magoo is on the loose.  We should put YOU on the stage in the Commons - I'll come down there and do that myself," she threatens.  The desk shifts as someone seems to have sat on its surface.  You peak under the thin space between the desk and the floor and you see a pair of red, stiletto high heels and some shapely ankles, one of which is home to a thin diamond anklet.

"Yes, your highness," the Sarlashkar responds.  "I am sorry.  So sorry."

"And so you should be, you wretch.  Find Xanadu Magoo.  Kill him.  Bring me his head."  Her words are venomous.

"But, miss," the Sarlashkar carefully retorts, "What about he access code?"

"Kill him.  Kill Straussberger.  Violently.  We shall move to plan B."

"Yes, your highness."

There is a pause.  The woman sitting on the desk stands up.  Two sets of footsteps make their way to the elevator.  You hear the sounds of the doors sliding shut and the elevator retreating.

You wait for a couple minutes and emerge from your hiding spot.

You notice that the woman who just left lost her anklet in the room.  It's lying on the floor by the desk.
