This is similar to the prison cell you found yourself in many hours ago with a few minor changes.  The walls are not cold stone but instead are padded and it is not icy cold but comfortably warm.  The grate above you is heavier.  Also, the seam outlining the door to the south is certainly visible.

And, oh yeah... there is a man cowered in the corner, his back to you.
> speak to prisoner

> speak to prisoner
You, as Blerk, mutter a feeble "Hey-o," while standing in the opposite corner of the room.  The man continues to rock back and forth, but utters nothing.
> speak to prisoner

> speak to prisoner
You muster a little more courage and speak a little more loudly, "Sir.  Can I hep?  'Et me hep.  Peas?"

Nothing.

Then, the man turns his head toward you ever so slightly.  He makes eyes contact with you and both of you let out an audible gasp.

"What the...?"

With the shaggy hair and the forlorn expression, you wouldn't recognize him, but you could never forget those steely blue eyes.  Sitting before you is Marcus Straussberger, your old high school friend and the current Dr. Dingo.
A voice booms over the loud speakers, "If you know the enemy and know yourself, your victory will not stand in doubt; if you know Heaven and know Earth, you may make your victory complete."  You recognize that quote as a Sun Tzu quote from the famous book 'Art of War'.
> speak to strauss

> speak to strauss
You try to explain yourself as best as you can in Blerk-talk...

He waits until you have finished and responds, "I have believed your story.  Now... you must believe mine.  These crazy Dingoes have stolen a nuclear weapon and plan on using it against the United States.  Only I have the activation code.  They have kidnapped me and have held me captive here for months.  I think they have commissioned the work of an imposter to replace me in the public eye so no one knows I am missing.  That man, even fooled you I believe.  You are here, Xanadu, to convince me to give you the code.  They have tortured me to get the codes, but I have not broken."  He pauses and takes a deep breath to collect himself.  "And, I shall not break, but I do not want to die.  If you fail to retrieve the code, they will not hesitate to kill you, but I will not give you the code either.  We need to help each other."

His story seems convincing enough...
