Well, it seems you have done it.  You have given your old high school friend, an American Hero, a chance at escaping.  He smiles wide at you and says, "Now, I wait to hear your escape.  From what you tell me, it seems like all hell will break loose when you finally make a run for it - I'm sure I'll hear it even from inside this cell.  But, remember, I cannot wait too long.  The risk is too great.  I'll give you thirty to forty-five minutes tops.  If I hear nothing by then..." he stops and looks solemnly into your eyes.  "I must assume you didn't make it.  Best of luck to you.  See you on the other side."
